Marfan syndrome (MFS) is an autosomal dominant connective tissue disorder. 
Diagnostic criteria of neonatal MFS (nMFS), the most severe form, are still 
debated. The aim of our study was to search for clinical and molecular 
prognostic factors that could be associated with length of survival. Probands 
ascertained via the framework of the Universal Marfan database-FBN1, diagnosed 
before the age of 1 y and presenting with cardiovascular features (aortic root 
dilatation or valvular insufficiency) were included in this study. Clinical and 
