survival (p = 0.03). We report the largest genotyped series of probands with MFS 
diagnosed before 1 y of life. In this population, factors significantly 
associated with shorter survival are presence of valvular insufficiencies or 
diaphragmatic hernia in addition to a mutation in exons 25 or 26.

