BACKGROUND: Family members of patients with established long-QT syndrome (LQTS) 
often lack definitive clinical findings, yet may have inherited an LQTS mutation 
and be at risk of sudden death. Genetic testing can identify mutations in 75% of 
patients with LQTS, but genetic testing of family members remains controversial.
